AUTOMATIC UPDATES
Download package: "apt install unattended-upgrades"
Set it up: "dpkg-reconfigure --priority=low unattended-upgrades"
CREATING ANOTHER USER WITH SUDO PRIVS
Create user: "adduser mrblue"
Add user to sudo group: "usermod -aG sudo bob"
CREATE KEY-PAIR/ID_RSA
create directory to store public key: "mkdir ~/.ssh && chmod 700 ~/.ssh"
Generate key pair on local system: "ssh-keygen -b 4096"
Gotto dir with public and private key: "cd .ssh"
Send public key to server: 
WINDOWS -> "scp $env:USERPROFILE/.ssh/id_rsa.pub bob@172.105.19.68:~/.ssh/authorized_keys"
LINUX -> "ssh-copy-id bob@172.105.19.68"
MACOS -> "scp ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub bob@172.105.19.68:~/.ssh/authorized_keys"
LOCKDOWN login (SSH)
Modify config file: "sudo nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config"
- change port: Uncomment and change deffault port 22 - > 789
- change address family: Uncomment and change "any" - > inet
- PermitRootLogin: yes - > no
- PaswordAuthentication: yes - > no
- Restart ssh service: "sudo systemctl restart sshd"
FIREWALL
Show open ports: "sudo ss -tupln"
Install Uncomplicated-Firewall(UFW): "sudo apt install ufw"
Allow port: "sudo ufw allow port"
Enable firewall: "sudo ufw enable"
Trytologin
NOTE: If you download other service make sure to update ufw rules
BLOCK PING
Edit file: "sudo nano /etc/ufw/before.rules"
Add line to "ok cimp codes for input": "-A ufw-before-input -p icmp --icmp-type echo-request -j DROP" 
Reload firewall: "sudo ufw reload" or reboot "sudo reboot"
